description:
PreschedProfile: Table storing pre-scheduling profile configurations for different cells in a radio access network.

- dateTime: Timestamp indicating when the configuration data was recorded.
- Area_Name: Name of the geographical area where the cell is located (e.g., NR_Balikpapan).
- CellId: Unique identifier for the cell site.
- Id2: Redundant cell identifier, possibly referencing another system.
- Id3:  A secondary identifier for the prescheduling profile.
- vsDataType: Type of data, specifying it as a prescheduling profile.
- vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format used.
- PreschedProfile.preschedulingDuration: Duration of the pre-scheduling period (in ms).
- PreschedProfile.reservedBy: Information about the entity or service that reserved the prescheduling profile.
- PreschedProfile.preschedulingSinrThreshold: Signal-to-interference-plus-noise ratio threshold for pre-scheduling.
- PreschedProfile.preschedulingDataSize: Size of data scheduled in advance (in KB, likely).
- PreschedProfile.preschedulingPeriod: Periodicity of the pre-scheduling (in ms or other unit).
- PreschedProfile.preschedProfileId: Unique identifier of the prescheduling profile.
